<subSubSection pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="temporal data">
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Temporal data.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Collected in January, March, May, August, September, and December.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
Inhabits the foothill evergreen forests in the Amazonian range from 970-1225 m a.s.l. Collected manually and with pitfall traps baited with carrion and human feces. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Kohlmann, B" journalOrPublisher="Giornale Italiano di Entomologia" pageId="271" pageNumber="272" pagination="343 - 382" title="El genero Dichotomius en Costa Rica." volume="8" year="1997">
Kohlmann and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Solís">Solis</normalizedToken>
(1997)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Solis, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="278" pageNumber="279" pagination="1 - 32" title="Checklist and Distribution Atlas of the Scarabaeinae of Costa Rica." volume="3482" year="2012">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Solís">Solis</normalizedToken>
and Kohlmann (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
, the previous records from Costa Rica are erroneous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
